facts.biology_mitochondria: Powerhouse of the cell. Produces ATP through cellular respiration

facts.biology_powerhouse of the cell: Mitochondria. Organelle that produces ATP energy
facts.biology_nucleus: Control center of the cell. Contains DNA and controls cell activities
facts.biology_ribosome: Protein factory. Synthesizes proteins from mRNA instructions
facts.biology_endoplasmic reticulum: Transport network. Processes and transports proteins

facts.biology_photosynthesis: 6CO₂ + 6H₂O + light → C₆H₁₂O₆ + 6O₂. Plants convert sunlight, water, and CO₂ into glucose and oxygen
facts.biology_cellular respiration: C₆H₁₂O₆ + 6O₂ → 6CO₂ + 6H₂O + ATP. Cells convert glucose and oxygen into energy, CO₂, and water
facts.biology_dna replication: DNA → 2 DNA copies. Process where DNA makes a copy of itself before cell division
facts.biology_transcription: DNA → mRNA. DNA code is copied into messenger RNA
facts.biology_translation: mRNA → Protein. Ribosomes read mRNA to build proteins

facts.biology_base pairing: A-T, G-C (DNA); A-U, G-C (RNA). Complementary base pairs in nucleic acids
facts.biology_double helix: DNA structure. Two strands wound around each other discovered by Watson & Crick
